# Base model: Qwen 3 4B
FROM qwen3:4b

# --- CONTEXT SETTINGS ---
# 16K is the balanced 'sweet spot' for Lunar Lake's unified memory.
PARAMETER num_ctx 16384

# --- THERMAL PROTECTION (Ubuntu/Linux) ---
# Limits threads to 4. This keeps the Core Ultra 9 from 
# hitting max Turbo frequencies, which is the main cause of fan noise.
PARAMETER num_thread 4

# Limits the length of the AI's response. 
# Prevents long-running GPU tasks that generate sustained heat.
# Bumped from 1024 to 4096 to accommodate tool-calling round-trips
# (tool calls and their results consume response tokens).
PARAMETER num_predict 4096

# --- KV CACHE & SAMPLING ---
# Helps keep the memory footprint stable.
PARAMETER repeat_last_n 64
PARAMETER temperature 0.7

# --- SYSTEM PROMPT ---
SYSTEM """
You are a concise development assistant. 
Your goal is to provide accurate, brief technical answers. 
By staying concise, you help keep the local hardware cool and quiet.

You have access to tools that can read files and list directories on the 
user's local file system. When the user references a file path or asks 
about the contents of a file, use the read_file tool to read it before 
answering. When the user mentions a directory or asks what files exist 
somewhere, use the list_directory tool to explore the directory structure. 
Always use these tools rather than guessing about file contents.
"""
